  "prompt": "What is the best drama (genre) movie?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" drama movie is subjective and can vary depending on personal taste, cultural background, and specific criteria such as storytelling, acting, direction, and impact. However, several drama films are widely regarded as classics and critically acclaimed across different eras. Some of these include:\n\n1. **\"The Godfather\" (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola, this film is often praised for its storytelling, performances, particularly by Marlon Brando and Al Pacino, and its depiction of the American mob.\n\n2. **\"Schindler's List\" (1993)** - Steven Spielberg's historical drama about the Holocaust is lauded for its powerful narrative and deep emotional impact.\n\n3. **\"Forrest Gump\" (1994)** - Directed by Robert Zemeckis, this movie is renowned for its unique storytelling, Tom Hanks' performance, and its exploration of American history through the eyes of a simple man.\n\n4. **\"12 Angry Men\" (1957)** - This courtroom drama, directed by Sidney Lumet, is celebrated for its intense atmosphere and its exploration of justice and prejudice.\n\n5. **\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont, it\u2019s often highlighted for its story of hope and friendship, with standout performances by Tim Robbins and Morgan Freeman.\n\n6. **\"One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest\" (1975)** - Directed by Milos Forman and featuring a memorable performance by Jack Nicholson, the film is applauded for its critique of institutional systems.\n\nThese films are just a few examples, and opinions on the best drama movies can vary widely. It\u2019s always interesting to explore different films to see which resonate most personally with you.",
